"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0809-1464298-adeleke-fourth-in-fastest-olympic-final-ever-pain\", \"text\": \"  Rhasidat Adeleke finished fourth in the fastest 400m Olympic final of all time, missing out on a medal in her debut Games.  Mikey Stafford is joined by Jessie Barr and Raf Diallo from the bowels of the Stade de France to analyse the final won by Marileidy Paulino of the Dominican Republic.  Jessie puts some perspective of the scale of the achievement and the level of competitors she was facing, while Raf gives us a sesne of what it was like to watch an Irish woman contend in an Olympic sprint final.  We also hear from the woman herself, who was disappointed to miss out on a medal.  There is a boost for the 4x400m relay team however, who will welcome Adeleke into the team for Saturday's final - the final event of the Olympics track meet.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"